# universaltea Food Store — Core Standards

## Project Context

This is a Next.js 15 (App Router) + Tailwind CSS + TypeScript + Supabase food store application.

## File Structure

```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js App Router pages
│   ├── admin/              # Admin panel routes
│   ├── chat/               # User chat
│   ├── gioi-thieu/         # About page
│   ├── login/              # Auth
│   ├── thuc-pham/          # Food catalog + detail
│   └── page.tsx            # Home
├── components/
│   ├── admin/              # Admin-specific
│   ├── auth/               # RoleGate, AuthGate
│   ├── food/               # FoodCard, etc.
│   └── layout/             # Header, Footer
└── lib/
    ├── supabase/           # client.ts, server.ts
    └── utils.ts            # cn(), formatPrice()
```

## Essential Rules

- Use `'use client'` for any component using hooks (useState, useEffect, useRouter, etc.)
- Server Components fetch data directly with `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/server`
- Client Components use `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/client`
- Always use `import type` for type-only imports
- Prefer `interface` over `type` for object shapes
- Never use `any` — use `unknown` with type guards
- Add `cursor-pointer` to all clickable elements
- Add `transition-colors` for hover effects (150-300ms)
- Format prices with `formatPrice()` from `@/lib/utils`
- Use Lucide React icons — never emoji icons
- Tailwind: `text-primary` = `#111111`, `primary` = `#111111`

## Component Patterns

- **Server Components**: async, no hooks, data fetching via server client
- **Client Components**: `'use client'`, useState/useEffect, browser client
- **Layouts**: wrap with `RoleGate` when role restriction needed
- **Auth pages**: use `AuthGate` wrapper for protected routes
- **Forms**: handle loading state, error display, disabled buttons

## Supabase Patterns

- Browser client: `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/client`
- Server client: `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/server`
- Realtime: `supabase.channel()` → `.on('postgres_changes', ...)` → `.subscribe()`
- RLS policies are already set in DB — queries work automatically
- Soft delete: use `supabase.from('foods').delete().eq('id', id)` — trigger sets `deleted_at`

## Style Guidelines

- Use `max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4` for page containers
- Use `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6` for card grids
- Mobile-first responsive: `hidden md:flex`, `md:hidden`
- Hover: `hover:text-primary`, `hover:bg-gray-50`, `hover:shadow-md`
- Focus: buttons have implicit focus styles via Tailwind
- Error states: `text-red-500 text-sm`
- Loading: `animate-spin` spinner, `opacity-50` for disabled buttons
